item.title: CVE-2024-6925|2024-09-08T06:00:03.340Z -- unknown -- truebooker
item.description: The TrueBooker WordPress plugin before 1.0.3 does not have CSRF check in place when updating its settings, which could allow attackers to make a logged in admin change them via a CSRF attack.

item.title: CVE-2024-6924|2024-09-08T06:00:03.155Z -- unknown -- truebooker
item.description: The TrueBooker WordPress plugin before 1.0.3 does not properly sanitise and escape a parameter before using it in a SQL statement via an AJAX action available to unauthenticated users, leading to a SQL injection.
